er%20too%20long%20%E2%80%94%20is%20shrinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idealized%20image%20of%20American%20life%20we%20know%20today%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdaily.jstor.org%2Fjames-truslow-adams-dreaming-american-dream%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrystallized%20in%20the%20country's%20collective%20imagination%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%201930s.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20idea%20that%20anyone%20can%20obtain%20a%20life%20that%20has%20the%20house%20with%20the%20white%20picket%20fence%2C%202.5%20children%2C%20a%20lucrative%20career%20at%20an%20office%20that's%20a%20reasonable%20distance%20away%2C%20and%20the%20occasional%20trip%20to%20an%20enviable%20vacation%20spot%20has%20loomed%20large%20in%20nearly%20every%20facet%20of%20cultural%20and%20political%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20just%20one%20problem%3A%20The%20once%20expansive%20vision%20is%20getting%20smaller.%20Not%20only%20is%20it%20harder%20to%20grab%20a%20piece%20of%20it%2C%20like%20a%20bag%20of%20chips%20or%20a%20roll%20of%20toilet%20paper%20that%20has%20less%20substance%20every%20time%20you%20buy%20it%2C%20but%20even%20nominally%20achieving%20the%20dream%20is%20leaving%20people%20unsatisfied.%20Americans%20are%20having%20fewer%20kids%2C%20their%20houses%20are%20getting%20smaller%2C%20they're%20schlepping%20further%20to%20work%2C%20and%20they're%20spending%20less%20time%20on%20vacation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20are%20taking%20notice%20of%20the%20diminishing%20returns.%20Among%20the%208%2C709%20US%20adults%20surveyed%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fshort-reads%2F2024%2F07%2F02%2Famericans-are-split-over-the-state-of-the-american-dream%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20April%208%20to%2014%2C%2041%25%20said%20that%20achieving%20the%20American%20dream%20was%20once%20possible%20but%20no%20longer.%20That's%20particularly%20true%20for%20younger%20Americans%3B%2018-%20to%2029-year-olds%20were%20the%20most%20likely%20to%20say%20that%20the%20American%20dream%20was%20never%20possible%2C%20and%20only%2039%25%20said%20that%20it's%20still%20possible.%20Their%20millennial%20counterparts%20felt%20similarly%2C%20though%20they%20were%20slightly%20more%20bullish%20on%20the%20possibility%20of%20the%20American%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F3hFNF%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22How%20Americans%20feel%20about%20achieving%20the%20American%20Dream%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22276%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Americans%20are%20increasingly%20less%20satisfied%20with%20their%20personal%20lives%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.gallup.com%2Fpoll%2F610133%2Fless-half-americans-satisfied-own-lives.aspx%23%3A~%3Atext%3DPercentages%2520of%2520Americans%2520who%2520are%2520satisfied%2520with%2520the%2520way%2520things%2Csatisfied%2520with%2520their%2520personal%2520life.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%20polling%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20January%20found.%20The%20share%20of%20Americans%20who%20are%20%26quot%3Bvery%20satisfied%26quot%3B%20with%20their%20personal%20lives%20has%20been%20plummeting%2C%20the%20poll%20found%2C%20and%20sits%20near%20record%20lows%20%E2%80%94%20other%20times%20it's%20gotten%20this%20bad%20were%20during%20the%20economic%20crisis%20of%202008%20and%20its%20fallout%20in%20the%20following%20years.%20And%20even%20among%20those%20who%20might%20have%20achieved%20the%20American%20dream%20%E2%80%94%20higher%20earners%20with%20college%20degrees%20%E2%80%94%20life%20satisfaction%20has%20slipped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECall%20it%20the%20shrinkflation%20of%20the%20American%20dream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20element%20of%20the%20American%20dream%20is%20owning%20a%20house.%20Having%20a%20roof%20over%20your%20head%20is%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20security%20and%20stability%3B%20research%20has%20found%20homeowners%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.surveymonkey.com%2Fcuriosity%2Fcnbc-financial-literacy-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eless%20stressed%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20their%20renter%20counterparts%2C%20and%20beyond%20having%20a%20place%20that%20they%20can%20call%20their%20own%2C%20they%20have%20growing%20equity.%20But%20nowadays%2C%20the%20homes%20that%20many%20Americans%20live%20in%20rarely%20have%20enough%20room%20for%20a%20big%20dog%20%E2%80%94%20much%20less%20a%20picket%20fence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202013%2C%20the%20median%20square%20footage%20of%20a%20new%20single-family%20housing%20unit%20was%20about%202%2C460.%20In%202015%2C%20new%20homes%20peaked%20at%20about%202%2C470%20square%20feet%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20spent%20the%20next%20six%20years%20shrinking.%20In%202021%2C%20homes%20started%20to%20slowly%20get%20bigger%20again%2C%20and%20then%20they%20once%20again%20constricted.%20By%202023%2C%20the%20figure%20had%20fallen%20to%20about%202%2C180%20square%20feet.%20An%20analysis%20by%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Home%20Builders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feyeonhousing.org%2F2024%2F09%2Fbedrooms-in-new-single-family-homes-in-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20share%20of%20single-family%20homes%20built%20with%20two%20bedrooms%20or%20fewer%20hit%20its%20highest%20level%20since%202012%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20share%20of%20new%20homes%20built%20with%20four%20bedrooms%20fell%20to%20its%20lowest%20level%20since%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FhYEqO%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Median%20square%20footage%20of%20new%20single-family%20housing%20units%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22410%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20homes%20getting%20a%20little%20smaller%20isn't%20necessarily%20a%20bad%20thing%20%E2%80%94%20many%20advocates%20for%20increasing%20the%20housing%20supply%20argue%20that%20the%20dedication%20to%20giant%20homes%20has%20made%20it%20tougher%20to%20build%20the%20number%20of%20new%20units%20that%20the%20country%20needs.%20But%20shrinking%20homes%20are%20coupled%20with%20another%20biting%20reality%3A%20Americans%20are%20paying%20more%20for%20less.%20In%20the%20same%20period%20that%20Americans%20have%20seen%20their%20homes%20shrink%2C%20home%20prices%20have%20grown%20by%20nearly%20%24200%2C000.%20The%20median%20listing%20price%20per%20square%20foot%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FMEDLISPRIPERSQUFEEUS%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24127%20in%202016%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20by%202024%2C%20that%20rose%20to%20%24224%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20Americans%20were%20shelling%20out%20more%20per%20square%20foot%2C%20even%20as%20their%20square%20footage%20decreased.%20By%20one%20measure%2C%20Americans%20now%20need%20to%20work%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftodayshomeowner.com%2Fmoving%2Fguides%2Fhours-worked-to-afford-mortgage%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E110%20hours%20a%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20their%20mortgages%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20mortgages%20eat%20up%20the%20bulk%20of%20their%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FnEPVc%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Median%20sales%20price%20of%20houses%20in%20the%20US%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22402%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20those%20prices%2C%20it's%20no%20wonder%20first-time%20homebuyers%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftypical-first-time-homebuyer-in-america-older-than-ever-before-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eolder%20than%20ever%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%20found%20that%20the%20median%20age%20of%20first-time%20homebuyers%20hit%2038%20in%202024%2C%20a%20record%20high.%20In%201981%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nar.realtor%2Fresearch-and-statistics%2Fresearch-reports%2Fhighlights-from-the-profile-of-home-buyers-and-sellers%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedian%20age%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20a%20first-time%20buyer%20was%2029%3B%20in%202014%2C%20it%20was%2031.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20all%20peaches%20and%20rainbows%20for%20American%20renters%2C%20either.%20The%20median%20rent%20price%20in%20the%20US%20is%20%242%2C035%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zillow.com%2Frental-manager%2Fmarket-trends%2Funited-states%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EZillow%3C%2Fa%3E%20found.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FRent.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERent.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rent.com%2Fresearch%2Faverage-rent-price-report%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20median%20rental%20asking%20prices%20hit%20about%20%241%2C619%20in%20October.%20That's%20nearly%20a%20%24300%20increase%20from%20May%202019.%20So%20if%20renters%20are%20paying%20more%2C%20surely%20they're%20still%20at%20least%20getting%20some%20bang%20for%20their%20buck%3F%20Nope%2C%20apartments%20are%20getting%20smaller%2C%20too.%20In%202016%2C%20the%20median%20square%20footage%20of%20a%20new%20unit%20in%20a%20building%20that%20had%20two%20or%20more%20units%20was%201%2C105%20square%20feet.%20Apartments%20have%20been%20shrinking%20since%20then%3A%20In%202023%2C%20new%20units%20were%20clocking%20in%20at%20a%20median%20of%201%2C020%20square%20feet%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20measure%20reached%20its%20lowest%20recorded%20level%20in%202021%20as%20housing%20prices%20and%20demand%20soared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FS4L2Y%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Median%20square%20feet%20per%20new%20unit%20in%20buildings%20with%202%20units%20or%20more%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20house%20is%20just%20a%20house%20until%20there%20are%20people%20in%20it%3B%20only%20then%2C%20the%20saying%20goes%2C%20is%20it%20a%20home.%20But%20increasingly%2C%20American%20homes%20are%20occupied%20by%20fewer%20people.%20Not%20only%20is%20there%20a%20slight%20rise%20in%20single%20people%20buying%20a%20house%2C%20but%20also%20the%20pitter-patter%20of%20babies'%20feet%20is%20becoming%20less%20common%20in%20the%20hallways%20of%20American%20homes%20these%20days.%20The%20share%20of%20homebuyers%20without%20a%20child%20under%2018%20in%20the%20house%20rose%20to%20a%20new%20high%20of%2073%25.%20That%20comes%20as%20Americans%20are%20having%20fewer%20kids%3A%20The%20average%20number%20of%20births%20per%20woman%20in%20the%20US%20has%20fallen%20from%20nearly%20four%20in%201960%20to%201.7%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F6tjgL%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Births%20per%20woman%20in%20the%20US%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22402%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20should%20come%20as%20no%20surprise%20that%20Americans%20are%20having%20fewer%20children%20given%20the%20economic%20and%20social%20pressures%20working%20against%20them.%20If%20it's%20hard%20for%20anyone%20to%20break%20into%20the%20ranks%20of%20homeowners%2C%20it's%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdinks-buy-homes-parents-spend-most-income-on-mortgage-childcare-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20difficult%20for%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Housing%20costs%20aren't%20the%20only%20deterrent%2C%20young%20parents%20are%20also%20floundering%20amid%20rising%20childcare%20costs%20and%20the%20loss%20of%20the%20social%20connections%20that%20are%20critical%20to%20raising%20kids.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20more%20Americans%20seem%20to%20be%20on%20board%20with%20choosing%20to%20go%20child-free.%20DINKs%20%E2%80%94%20double-income%2C%20no-kid%20couples%20%E2%80%94%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-dinks-winning-childfree-economy-finances-income-vacation-retirement-kids-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeen%20on%20the%20cultural%20rise%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20just%20because%20it's%20harder%20for%20people%20with%20kids%20and%20more%20acceptable%20to%20forgo%20them%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20people%20are%20giving%20up%20on%20starting%20a%20family.%20Many%20Americans%20want%20to%20have%20children%20or%20have%20even%20more%20kids%2C%20but%20it's%20out%20of%20reach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKaren%20Benjamin%20Guzzo%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20at%20Chapel%20Hill%20who's%20researched%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20number%20of%20children%20Americans%20intend%20to%20have%20versus%20their%20ultimate%20childbearing%2C%20told%20me%20that%20having%20kids%20is%20often%20seen%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Blast%20step%26quot%3B%20in%20accomplishing%20the%20American%20dream.%20You%20go%20to%20college%2C%20you%20line%20up%20a%20good%20job%2C%20you%20get%20married%2C%20you%20buy%20a%20house%2C%20and%20then%20you%20fill%20it%20with%20kids.%20There's%20a%20problem%2C%20though.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20step%20along%20the%20way%20has%20become%20less%20and%20less%20predictable%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FamoFq%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Women's%20intended%20births%20vs.%20actual%20children%20by%20birth%20cohort%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22434%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EGuzzo's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC10312362%2F%23S13%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20found%2C%20in%20part%2C%20that%20Americans%20still%20expect%20to%20have%20children%20%E2%80%94%20they%20just%20don't%20actually%20have%20them.%20The%20way%20Guzzo%20describes%20it%20is%20many%20Americans%20want%20kids%2C%20but%20with%20an%20asterisk%3A%20They%20want%20kids%20if%20they%20can%20find%20a%20good%20partner%2C%20a%20good%20job%20with%20family%20leave%20and%20enough%20pay%20to%20afford%20childcare%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20need%20to%20feel%20confident%20that%20the%20next%2025%20years%20of%20their%20lives%20and%20the%20world%20in%20which%20their%20children%20will%20be%20raised%20and%20growing%20and%20becoming%20adults%20on%20their%20own.%20They%20need%20to%20feel%20confident%20about%20those%2C%26quot%3B%20Guzzo%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20do%20not%20do%20a%20good%20job%20right%20now%20in%20the%20United%20States%20of%20making%20people%20feel%20confident%20about%20their%20futures.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20American%20dream%20is%20the%20ability%20to%20actually%20enjoy%20it.%20You%20can%20come%20home%20for%20dinner%2C%20spend%20a%20nice%20evening%20with%20your%20family%2C%20and%20maybe%20enjoy%20some%20ice%20cream%20in%20front%20of%20the%20TV%20before%20heading%20to%20bed%20at%20a%20reasonable%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20for%20many%20people%2C%20the%20free%20time%20is%20getting%20sapped%20by%20a%20mind-numbing%20commute.%20The%20average%20travel%20time%20to%20work%20in%201990%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2FCensus%2Fnewsroom%2Fc-span%2F2013%2F20130308_cspan_commuting.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E22.4%20minutes%20one%20way%3C%2Fa%3E.%20By%202023%2C%20it%20rose%20to%2026.8%20minutes.%20That%20may%20not%20sound%20like%20a%20lot%2C%20but%20that%20adds%20up%20to%20nearly%204.5%20hours%20a%20week%20just%20commuting%20to%20work%2C%20or%20about%2010%20days%20a%20year%2C%20assuming%20they%20went%20in%20every%20workday.%20Even%20if%20they're%20going%20into%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20that's%20still%20nearly%202.7%20hours%20a%20week%20commuting%2C%20or%20the%20equivalent%20of%20almost%206%20full%20days%20a%20year.%20Meanwhile%2C%20in%201990%2C%20Americans%20spent%20just%20about%203.7%20hours%20a%20week%20commuting%20%E2%80%94%20about%2044%20minutes%20less%20a%20week.%20That's%20a%20whole%20episode%20of%20%26quot%3BReal%20Housewives.%26quot%3B%20Even%20on%20a%20small%20scale%2C%20research%20has%20found%20that%20every%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommuting-work-job-satisfaction-2017-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eminute%20added%20to%20a%20commute%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20reduce%20one's%20satisfaction%20with%20both%20their%20job%20and%20their%20leisure%20time.%20Most%20Americans%20commuting%20are%20doing%20so%20by%20car%2C%20which%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommuting-by-car-is-hurting-peoples-mental-health-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ealso%20weigh%20on%20workers'%20mental%20health%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20well%20they're%20sleeping.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FkSTu2%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Average%20one-way%20commute%20time%20in%20minutes%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22428%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20as%20more%20Americans%20have%20moved%20away%20from%20urban%20cores%20%E2%80%94%20perhaps%20in%20pursuit%20of%20buying%20a%20house%20in%20cheaper%20areas%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-high-earners-moved-office-work-from-home-remote-work-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eliving%20farther%20from%20work%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Young%20families%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-young-kids-families-fleeing-big-cities-urban-doom-loop-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20fled%3C%2Fa%3E%20larger%20urban%20areas%20and%20are%20finding%20themselves%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-priced-out-of-cities-into-suburbs-housing-crisis-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efarthest%20reaches%20of%20suburbia%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20you%20want%20the%20American%20dream%20of%20that%20larger%2C%20cheaper%20house%2C%20you%20might%20be%20paying%20for%20it%20in%20minutes%20stuck%20behind%20the%20wheel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReveling%20in%20the%20American%20dream%20also%20includes%20unwinding%20away%20from%20that%20house%20and%20job.%20But%20even%20as%20more%20Americans%20have%20access%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdata.bls.gov%2Fpdq%2FSurveyOutputServlet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaid%20vacation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20they're%20taking%20it.%20In%20July%201980%2C%20over%2010%20million%20working%20Americans%20were%20on%20vacation.%20At%20the%20height%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20that%20number%20had%20halved.%20And%20even%20as%20more%20Americans%20went%20on%20vacation%20in%20July%20post-2020%2C%20the%20number%20of%20workers%20vacationing%20in%20July%20has%20essentially%20plateaued%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FRdrVS%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Number%20of%20working%20Americans%20on%20vacation%20in%20July%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22402%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2F02%2F10%2Fdisappearing-vacation-days%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20extensive%20analysis%20of%20eroding%20vacation%20time%2C%20some%20of%20that%20might%20be%20chalked%20up%20to%20another%20form%20of%20shrinkflation%3A%20Workers%20saving%20their%20vacation%20days%20for%20when%20they're%20feeling%20sick.%20In%20a%20very%20Dickensian%20twist%2C%20Americans%20might%20not%20be%20going%20on%20vacation%20because%20they're%20too%20busy%20being%20sick%20or%20caring%20for%20their%20ill%20kids%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20this%20is%20not%20to%20say%20that%20the%20American%20dream%20has%20gone%20extinct%2C%20but%20there's%20a%20marked%20shift%20from%20the%20idea%20that%20things%20will%20get%20better%20for%20each%20successive%20generation.%20In%20a%20country%20where%20growth%2C%20expansion%2C%20and%20constantly%20improving%20your%20lot%20%E2%80%94%20and%20your%20family's%20lot%20%E2%80%94%20are%20North%20Stars%2C%20a%20diminishing%20and%20sickly%20American%20dream%20is%20a%20bit%20of%20an%20existential%20downer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20in%20a%20March%202023%20survey%20of%201%2C019%20American%20adults%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fs.wsj.net%2Fpublic%2Fresources%2Fdocuments%2FWSJ_NORC_Topline_EconQuestionsMarch2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20and%20NORC%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2078%25%20of%20respondents%20said%20they%20were%20not%20confident%20that%20life%20would%20be%20better%20for%20their%20kids'%20generation.%20The%20share%20not%20confident%20their%20kids'%20lives%20will%20be%20better%20has%20soared%20over%20the%20past%20few%20decades%3B%20in%202000%20just%2042%25%20said%20the%20same.%20In%20short%3A%20Many%20Americans%20are%20feeling%20like%20the%20dream%20is%20slipping%20through%20their%20fingers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGuzzo%20said%20that%20we're%20seeing%20a%20bifurcation%20of%20the%20American%20dream.%20For%20the%20ultrawealthy%2C%20the%20ability%20to%20accumulate%20the%20markers%20of%20the%20dream%20has%20never%20been%20easier.%20The%20top%201%25%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Freleases%2Fz1%2Fdataviz%2Fdfa%2Fdistribute%2Fchart%2F%23quarter%3A127%3Bseries%3AReal%2520estate%3Bdemographic%3Anetworth%3Bpopulation%3A1%2C3%2C5%2C7%2C9%3Bunits%3Ashares%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eholds%20just%20over%2013%25%20of%20all%20real%20estate%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20dollar%20value%20in%20the%20US%2C%20while%20the%20bottom%2050%25%20holds%20just%20about%2010%25.%20And%2C%20as%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20Atlanta%20recounted%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Fmonetarypolicy%2Ffiles%2FBeigeBook_20241204.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDecember%20Beige%20Book%20round-up%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20lower-%20and%20middle-income%20consumers%20are%20scaling%20back%20their%20vacation%20plans%3B%20they're%20renting%20homes%20for%20multiple%20families%20and%20eating%20in%20rather%20than%20splashing%20out%20on%20hotels%20or%20fancy%20restaurants.%20Instead%2C%20the%20strength%20in%20tourism%20spending%20comes%20from%20those%20higher-income%20consumers%20exploring%20and%20going%20on%20cruises.%20For%20Americans%20in%20the%20middle%2C%20those%20who%20might%20have%20the%20college%20degree%20and%20career%20that%20could%20set%20them%20on%20that%20trajectory%2C%20the%20dream%20is%20still%20possible%2C%20though%20it%20may%20come%20later%20in%20life.%20But%20Guzzo%20said%20others%2C%20especially%20younger%20men%20without%20college%20degrees%2C%20feel%20the%20American%20dream%20has%20been%20pulled%20out%20from%20beneath%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20there's%20a%20bittersweet%20parallel%20running%20alongside%20the%20shrinking%20of%20the%20American%20dream.%20For%20decades%2C%20things%20like%20homeownership%20or%20formal%20recognition%20of%20marriage%20were%20out%20of%20grasp%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20expressly%20forbidden%20%E2%80%94%20for%20many%20marginalized%20groups.%20It's%20only%20in%20recent%20history%20that%20LGBTQ%2B%20Americans%20and%20Americans%20of%20color%20have%20been%20able%20to%20somewhat%20catch%20up%20to%20their%20straight%20and%20white%20peers.%20But%20now%20that%20the%20American%20dream%20is%20within%20reach%20for%20these%20people%2C%20it's%20already%20shrinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjuliana-kaplan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJuliana%20Kaplan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20labor%20and%20inequality%20reporter%20on%20Business%20Insider's%20economy%20team.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-dream-shrinking-smaller-homes-fewer-kids-vacation-time-commutes-2024-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734426421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6751de1a8fb3f94e50739e6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-dream-shrinking-smaller-homes-fewer-kids-vacation-time-commutes-2024-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22From%20tinier%20homes%20and%20fewer%20kids%20to%20less%20vacation%20time%20and%20longer%20commutes%2C%20America's%20aspirations%20are%20getting%20smaller%20by%20the%20day.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-dream-shrinking-smaller-home