0a%20way%20to%20have%20conversations%20about%20complicated%20issues%2C%20like%20national%20politics%2C%20but%20in%20context%20with%20people%20I%20actually%20know%20and%20care%20about%2C%26quot%3B%20Kramer%2C%20who%20is%20the%20head%20of%20editorial%20at%20New_%20Public%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20research%20and%20development%20lab%20focusing%20on%20reimagining%20social%20media%2C%20tells%20me.%20The%20success%20of%20the%20server%20has%20also%20informed%20how%20he%20thinks%20about%20ways%20to%20reform%20the%20social%20web.%20On%20election%20night%2C%20for%20example%2C%20using%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsocial-media-dead-instagram-tiktok-bereal-replaced-group-chats-messaging-2023-8%3Futm_source%3Dtwitter%26utm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_campaign%3Dbusiness-sf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egroup%20chat%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20less%20about%20scoring%20points%20with%20a%20quippy%20tweet%20and%20%26quot%3Bmore%20about%20checking%20in%20with%20each%20other%20and%20commiserating%20about%20our%20experience%2C%20rather%20than%20whatever%20you%20might%20take%20to%20Twitter%20to%20talk%20about%20to%20check%20in%20with%20the%20broader%20zeitgeist.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20month%20or%20so%20since%20the%202024%20election%2C%20thousands%20have%20abandoned%20or%20deactivated%20their%20X%20accounts%2C%20taking%20issue%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftwitter-x-elon-musk-startup-competitition-town-square-election-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk's%3C%2Fa%3E%20move%20to%20use%20the%20platform%20as%20a%20tool%20to%20reelect%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20as%20they%20seek%20new%20ways%20to%20connect%20and%20share%20information.%20Bluesky%2C%20which%20saw%20its%20users%20grow%20110%25%20in%20November%20according%20to%20market%20intelligence%20firm%20Sensor%20Tower%2C%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20most%20promising%20replacement%20among%20many%20progressives%2C%20journalists%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstartup-helping-people-leave-twitter-bluesky-tweets-perserve-social-media-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ESwifties%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20it%20allows%20people%20to%20easily%20share%20links%20and%20doesn't%20rely%20as%20heavily%20on%20algorithmic%20delivery%20of%20posts%20as%20platforms%20like%20Facebook%2C%20X%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ban-details-when-how-legal-cases-trump-options%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETikTok%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20come%20to.%20But%20some%20are%20turning%20further%20inward%20to%20smaller%20group%20chats%2C%20either%20via%20text%20message%20or%20on%20platforms%20like%20Discord%2C%20WhatsApp%2C%20and%20Signal%2C%20where%20they%20can%20have%20conversations%20more%20privately%20and%20free%20of%20algorithmic%20determinations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20all%20part%20of%20the%20larger%2C%20ongoing%20fracturing%20of%20our%20social%20media%20landscape.%20For%20a%20decade%2C%20Twitter%20proved%20to%20be%20the%20room%20where%20news%20broke.%20Other%20upstarts%20launched%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-marc-andreessen-tesla-spacex-management-leadership-tech-talent-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElon%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%20bought%20the%20platform%20in%202022%20and%20tried%20to%20compete%2C%20luring%20people%20with%20promises%20of%20moderation%20and%20civility%2C%20but%20ultimately%20folded%2C%20largely%20because%20they%20weren't%20very%20fun%20or%20lacked%20the%20momentum%20created%20by%20the%20kind%20of%20power%20users%20that%20propelled%20the%20old%20Twitter.%20But%20for%20many%2C%20there's%20still%20safety%20in%20the%20smaller%20group%20chats%2C%20which%20take%20the%20form%20of%20your%20friends%20who%20like%20to%20shit%20talk%20in%20an%20iMessage%20chain%20or%20topic-focused%2C%20larger%20chats%20on%20apps%20like%20Discord%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fx-lesspopular-with-teens-more-use-whatsapp-meta-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhatsApp%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGroup%20chats%20have%20been%20quite%20valued%2C%26quot%3B%20Kate%20Mannell%2C%20a%20research%20fellow%20with%20the%20ARC%20Centre%20of%20Excellence%20for%20the%20Digital%20Child%20at%20Deakin%20University%20in%20Australia%2C%20tells%20me.%20They%20allow%20people%20to%20chat%20with%20selected%20friends%2C%20family%20members%2C%20or%20colleagues%20to%20have%20much%20%26quot%3Bmore%20context-specific%20kinds%20of%20conversations%2C%20which%20I%20think%20is%20much%20more%20reflective%20of%20the%20way%20that%20our%20social%20groups%20actually%20exist%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20this%20kind%20of%20flattening%26quot%3B%20that%20happens%20on%20social%20media.%20When%20people%20accumulate%20large%20followings%20on%20social%20media%2C%20they%20run%20into%20context%20collapse%2C%20she%20says.%20The%20communication%20breakdown%20happens%20as%20the%20social%20platforms%20launched%20in%20the%202000s%20have%20taken%20on%20larger%20lives%20than%20anyone%20anticipated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20contrast%2C%20some%20more%20exclusive%20chats%20are%20seen%20as%20cozy%2C%20safe%20spaces.%20Most%20of%20Discord's%20servers%20are%20made%20up%20of%20fewer%20than%2010%20people%2C%20Savannah%20Badalich%2C%20the%20senior%20director%20of%20policy%20at%20Discord%2C%20tells%20me.%20The%20company%20has%20200%20million%20active%20users%2C%20up%20from%20100%20million%20in%202020.%20What%20started%20as%20a%20place%20to%20hang%20with%20friends%20while%20playing%20video%20games%20still%20incentivizes%20interacting%20over%20lurking%20or%20building%20up%20big%20followings.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20that%20endless%20doomscrolling%2C%26quot%3B%20Badalich%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20have%20that%20place%20where%20you're%20passively%20consuming%20content.%20Discord%20is%20about%20real-time%20interaction.%26quot%3B%20And%20interacting%20among%20smaller%20groups%20may%20be%20more%20natural.%20Research%20by%20the%20psychologist%20Robin%20Dunbar%20in%20the%201990s%20found%20that%20humans%20could%20cognitively%20maintain%20about%20150%20meaningful%20relationships.%20More%20recent%20research%20has%20questioned%20that%20determination%2C%20but%20any%20person%20overburdened%20by%20our%20digital%20age%20can%20surely%20tell%20you%20that%20you%20can%20only%20show%20up%20authentically%20and%20substantially%20in%20person%20for%20a%20small%20subset%20of%20the%20people%20you%20follow%20online.%20A%202024%20study%2C%20conducted%20by%20Dunbar%20and%20the%20telecommunications%20company%20Vodafone%2C%20found%20that%20the%20average%20person%20in%20the%20UK%20was%20part%20of%2083%20group%20chats%20across%20all%20platforms%2C%20with%20a%20quarter%20of%20people%20using%20group%20chats%20more%20often%20than%20one-to-one%20messages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20hosting%20group%20chats%2C%20WhatsApp%20has%20tried%20more%20recently%20to%20position%20itself%20as%20a%20place%20for%20news%2C%20giving%20publishers%20the%20ability%20to%20send%20headlines%20directly%20to%20followers.%20News%20organizations%20like%20MSNBC%2C%20Reuters%2C%20and%20Telemundo%20have%20channels.%20CNN%20has%20nearly%2015%20million%20followers%2C%20while%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20has%20about%2013%20million.%20Several%20publishers%20recently%20told%20the%20Times%20that%20they%20were%20seeing%20growth%20and%20traffic%20come%20from%20WhatsApp%2C%20but%20the%20channels%20have%20yet%20to%20rival%20sources%20like%20Google%20or%20Facebook.%20While%20it%20gives%20them%20the%20power%20to%20connect%20to%20readers%2C%20WhatsApp%20is%20owned%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-feud-elon-musk-openai-public-for-profit-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20a%20fraught%20history%20of%20hooking%20media%20companies%20and%20making%20them%20dependent%20on%20traffic%20on%20its%20social%20platforms%20only%20to%20later%20de-emphasize%20their%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVictoria%20Usher%2C%20the%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20Gingermay%2C%20a%20B2B%20tech%20communications%20firm%2C%20says%20she's%20in%20several%20large%2C%20business-focused%20group%20chats%20on%20WhatsApp.%20Usher%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20even%20found%20these%20chats%20were%20a%20way%20to%20get%20news%20about%20the%20US%20election%20%26quot%3Bimmediately.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20way%2C%20the%20group%20chats%20are%20her%20way%20of%20optimizing%20news%20and%20analysis%20of%20it%2C%20and%20it%20works%20because%20there's%20a%20deep%20sense%20of%20trust%20between%20those%20in%20the%20chat%20that%20doesn't%20exist%20when%20scrolling%20X.%20%26quot%3BI%20prefer%20it%20to%20an%20algorithm%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20going%20to%20be%20stories%20that%20I%20will%20find%20interesting.%26quot%3B%20She%20thinks%20they%20deliver%20information%20better%20than%20LinkedIn%2C%20where%20people%20have%20taken%20to%20writing%20posts%20in%20classic%20LinkedIn%20style%20to%20please%20the%20algorithm%20%E2%80%94%20which%20can%20be%20both%20self-serving%20and%20cringe.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20it's%20a%20truthful%20channel%2C%26quot%3B%20Usher%20says.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20trying%20to%20create%20a%20picture%20of%20how%20they%20want%20to%20be%20seen%20personally.%20Within%20WhatsApp%20groups%20or%20Signal%2C%20people%20are%20much%20more%20likely%20to%20post%20what%20they%20actually%20feel%20about%20something.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20candid%20nature%20of%20group%20chats%20%E2%80%94%20which%20some%20have%20called%20the%20last%20safe%20spaces%20in%20society%20today%20%E2%80%94%20gives%20them%20value%20and%20tethers%20people%20with%20looser%20connections%20together%2C%20but%20that%20can%20also%20make%20them%20unwieldy.%20Some%20of%20the%20larger%20group%20chats%2C%20like%20those%20on%20Discord%2C%20have%20moderation%20and%20rules.%20But%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20just%20chatting%20with%20your%20friends%20or%20family%2C%20there's%20largely%20no%20established%20group-chat%20etiquette.%20Group%20chats%20can%20languish%20for%20years%3B%20there's%20no%20playbook%20for%20leaving%20or%20kicking%20out%20someone%20who's%20no%20longer%20close%20to%20the%20core%20group.%20If%20a%20couple%20breaks%20up%2C%20who%20gets%20the%20group%20chat%3F%20How%20many%20memes%20is%20a%20person%20allowed%20to%20send%20a%20day%3F%20What%20happens%20when%20the%20group%20texts%20get%20leaked%3F%20There's%20often%20%26quot%3Bno%20external%20moderator%20to%20come%20in%20and%20say%2C%20'That's%20not%20how%20we%20do%20things%2C'%26quot%3B%20Mannell%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKramer%2C%20while%20he%20likes%20his%20Discord%20chat%2C%20is%20optimistic%20about%20the%20future%20of%20groups%20and%20new%20social%20networks.%20He%20says%20he's%20also%20taken%20over%20a%20community%20Facebook%20group%20for%20his%20neighborhood%20that%20was%20inactive%20and%20made%20more%20connections%20with%20his%20neighbors.%20We're%20in%20a%20moment%20where%20massive%20change%20could%20come%20to%20our%20chats%20and%20our%20social%20networks.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20been%20a%20social%20internet%20for%2030%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kramer.%20But%20there's%20%26quot%3Bso%20much%20room%20for%20innovation%20and%20new%20exciting%20and%20alternative%20options.%26quot%3B%20But%20his%20group%20chat%20might%20still%20have%20the%20best%20vibes%20of%20all.%20Messaging%20there%20%26quot%3Bhas%20less%20to%20do%20with%20being%20right%20and%20scoring%20points%26quot%3B%20than%20on%20social%20media%2C%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20so%20much%20value%20to%20me%20on%20a%20personal%20level%2C%20as%20a%20place%20of%20real%20support.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Famanda-hoover%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EAmanda%20Hoover%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20corres