o%20financial%20plan%20before%20their%20spouse's%20death.%20The%20firm%20surveyed%20a%20national%20sample%20of%20422%20female%20widows%20in%20May%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELauer%20wishes%20her%20%26quot%3Bmarriage%20license%20came%20with%20instructions%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Steve%20died%20unexpectedly%2C%20and%20Lauer%20said%20she%20didn't%20have%20enough%20knowledge%20about%20the%20probate%20and%20asset-division%20process%2C%20or%20how%20it%20would%20affect%20her%20livelihood%20as%20the%20surviving%20spouse.%20She%20advises%20other%20married%20people%20to%20write%20a%20will%20and%20make%20a%20financial%20plan%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224da78b1e-54b4-42ca-9875-707ba997e1a4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20protect%20your%20finances%20if%20your%20spouse%20dies%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228192%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20Robert%20and%20his%20late%20wife%20sits%20in%20a%20rocking%20chair%20by%20a%20Christmas%20Tree.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6760878ad0de6a4f27d3362e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225464%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20photo%20of%20Robert%20Berkely%20and%20his%20late%20wife%2C%20Lourdes%2C%20sits%20in%20a%20rocking%20chair%20by%20a%20Christmas%20tree.%3Cp%3ESaul%20Martinez%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOrnstein%20said%20there%20are%20a%20few%20key%20ways%20that%20Americans%20can%20financially%20protect%20themselves%20if%20their%20spouse%20dies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20step%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprotect-my-assets-income-streams-getting-will-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreating%20a%20will%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20having%20regular%20conversations%20about%20finances%20as%20a%20couple.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Flife-insurance%2Fbest-life-insurance-companies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elife-insurance%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20people%20can%20buy%20or%20opt%20in%20to%20through%20their%20employer%20%E2%80%94%20can%20provide%20further%20financial%20security%20to%20a%20deceased%20person's%20family%20after%20their%20death.%20Typically%2C%20people%20pay%20a%20regular%20premium%20for%20the%20insurance%20throughout%20their%20career%20and%20can%20name%20a%20spouse%20or%20children%20as%20their%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrnstein%20told%20BI%20that%20widows%20and%20widowers%20should%20work%20with%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-inheritance-can-destroy-family-be-gift-estate-planning-attorney-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestate-planning%20attorney%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20financial%20advisor%2C%20and%20tax%20professional%20directly%20after%20their%20spouse%20dies.%20He%20added%20that%2C%20when%20preparing%20for%20those%20meetings%2C%20it's%20best%20to%20collect%20as%20many%20legal%20and%20financial%20documents%20as%20possible%3A%20a%20death%20certificate%2C%20a%20marriage%20license%2C%20bank%20statements%2C%20tax%20returns%2C%20benefits%20paperwork%2C%20insurance%20policies%2C%20and%20a%20will.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20an%20attorney%20and%20financial%20advisor%2C%20widows%20and%20widowers%20should%20apply%20%E2%80%94%20or%20reapply%20%E2%80%94%20for%20benefits%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-social-security-regrets-401k-divorce-moving-financial-mistakes-aarp-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20pensions%2C%20Ornstein%20said.%20They%20may%20be%20entitled%20to%20spousal%20benefits%20or%20higher%20monthly%20government%20aid.%20He%20added%20that%20a%20surviving%20spouse%20would%20likely%20have%20to%20transfer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fwhat-are-assets%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eownership%20of%20assets%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20a%20house%2C%20credit%20card%2C%20retirement%20account%2C%20or%20loan%20to%20themself%20or%20another%20family%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTake%20things%20one%20step%20at%20a%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20a%20follow-up%20email.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20normal%20to%20feel%20stressed%2C%20overwhelmed%2C%20and%20anxious%20in%20this%20situation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20not%20all%20widows%20or%20widowers%20have%20regrets%20about%20their%20money%20habits%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20in%20a%20precarious%20financial%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20back%20on%20his%2048%20years%20of%20marriage%2C%20Robert%20Berkeley%20feels%20good%20about%20how%20he%20spent%20his%20money.%20He%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Lourdes%2C%20spent%20decades%20traveling%2C%20dining%20at%20their%20favorite%20restaurants%2C%20and%20hosting%20big%20family%20holiday%20gatherings%20in%20their%20eastern%20North%20Carolina%20home.%20After%20their%20respective%20careers%20as%20an%20intelligence%20analyst%20and%20a%20dental%20hygienist%2C%20the%20couple%20decided%20to%20retire%20in%20their%2060s%20%E2%80%94%20living%20largely%20on%20their%20monthly%20Social%20Security%20checks%20and%20the%20few%20thousand%20dollars%20they%20had%20saved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwelve%20years%20later%2C%20in%202022%2C%20Lourdes%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20cancer.%20The%20disease%20was%20aggressive%2C%20and%20she%20died%20within%20a%20couple%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emonths.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2078%2C%20Berkeley%20is%20struggling%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%20He%20and%20his%20wife%20didn't%20have%20a%20life-insurance%20policy%20or%20robust%20savings.%20He%20said%20it's%20been%20difficult%20to%20afford%20housing%2C%20utilities%2C%20groceries%2C%20and%20transportation%20without%20two%20Social%20Security%20incomes.%20Berkeley%20receives%20a%20%241%2C650%20monthly%20payment%2C%20but%20he's%20in%20debt%20and%20behind%20on%20bills.%20He's%20hoping%20the%20part-time%20security%20guard%20job%20he%20landed%20recent