ign-3-1733937411-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733937411-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733937411-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F12%2FUntitled-design-3-1733937411-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-388809%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWhen%20Nishad%20switched%20to%20farming%2C%20he%20chose%20to%20grow%20butterfly%20pea%20flowers%20instead%20of%20traditional%20crops.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20Nishad%20started%20with%20butterfly%20peas%20and%20has%20since%20expanded%20his%20product%20line%20to%20include%20rose%2C%20hibiscus%2C%20marigold%2C%20calendula%2C%20lemongrass%2C%20spearmint%2C%20tulsi%2C%20jasmine%2C%20chamomile%2C%20and%20ginger%20%E2%80%94%20all%20used%20for%20making%20teas%2C%20syrups%2C%20or%20preserves.%20%E2%80%9CI%20earn%20around%20a%20lakh%20rupees%20a%20month%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Nishad%2C%20with%20a%20turnover%20ranging%20between%2020%20to%2030%20tonnes%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20established%20a%20small%20centre%20outside%20the%20village%20where%20farmers%20from%20the%20nearby%20area%20come%20to%20sell%20their%20harvested%20flowers%20twice%20a%20day%20%E2%80%94%20once%20in%20the%20morning%20and%20once%20in%20the%20evening.%20These%20fresh%20flowers%20are%20dehydrated%20within%2012%20to%2015%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20use%20of%20solar%20dryers%20was%20a%20key%20turning%20point%20in%20Nishad%E2%80%99s%20business%20venture.%20Initially%2C%20he%20dried%20flowers%20in%20an%20open%20environment%2C%20exposed%20to%20dust%2C%20bird%20droppings%2C%20and%20unpredictable%20weather%20conditions%2C%20which%20could%20damage%20the%20product.%20Eventually%2C%20he%20invested%20in%20a%20solar%20dryer%20costing%20Rs%206