rame%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20for%20Chef%20Jatin%2C%20this%20place%20features%20on%20his%20list%20of%20favourites.%20Not%20just%20this%20eatery%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CPandara%20Road%20has%20been%20a%20go-to%20spot%20for%20ages.%20Whenever%20I%20used%20to%20visit%20Delhi%2C%20a%20visit%20to%20Pandara%20Road%20with%20the%20family%20was%20a%20must.%20That%20flavour%20of%20butter%20chicken%20is%20etched%20in%20my%20head.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20Moti%20Mahal%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20OG%20butter%20chicken%20spot!%20It%20was%20here%20that%20the%20seminal%20discovery%20happened%20post-Partition.%20The%20story%20goes%20that%20Kundan%20Lal%20Gujral%2C%20a%20cloth%20merchant%E2%80%99s%20son%20began%20working%20at%20an%20eatery%20in%20Peshawar%E2%80%99s%20Gora%20Bazaar%20(in%20present-day%20Pakistan)%20in%20the%20early%201900s.%20After%20Partition%2C%20in%201947%2C%20Kundan%20Lal%20Gujral%20travelled%20to%20Delhi%20with%20his%20family%20as%20refugees%2C%20where%20Kundan%20reestablished%20Moti%20Mahal%20in%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Daryaganj.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20history%20tells%20us%2C%20the%20butter%20chicken%20was%20born%20out%20of%20the%20worry%20of%20having%20cooked%20chicken%20dry%20out.%20Kundan%20was%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20a%20sauce%20with%20which%20he%20could%20rehydrate%20them.%20His%20solution%20lay%20in%20the%20butter%20sauce%2C%20which%20eventually%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F356862%2Forigin-story-chicken-tikka-masala-history-shish-mahal-scotland-glasgow-karims-delhi-ranveer-brar-recipe%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egave%20history%20its%20best%20dish%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%201950s%20heyday%2C%20Gujral%E2%80%99s%20Moti%20Mahal%20was%20extremely%20popular%20with%20celebrities%20and%20world%20leaders%2C%20including%20Zakir%20Hussain%2C%20Jawahar%20Lal%20Nehru%2C%20Richard%20Nixon%20and%20John%